=============
 Description
=============

This is a program used by the C2P1 association (www.c2p1.fr) to manage
the student presences coming to the tutoring sessions.

===============
 Installation
===============

Just use the binary ;)

==========
 Use
==========

You'll need the student info as a CSV file in DOS/WIN format
(not MAC format insofar as it seems it's not \n line-terminated).

For your information, here is the description and order of the columns,
the ones used by this software are marked with a [*]
- C2P1 Number [*]
- Phone number
- Last Name [*]
- First Name [*]
- "Primant" or "Doublant"
- "adhérent" (or not...)
- Student number, STARTING WITH "5" ! [*]
- Date of birth, jjmmaa format
- scolarship or not
- email
- price paid
- mentoring
- Khôlle
- SP section

==============
 COMPILATION
==============

You'll need wxWidgets to compile it:
- Under MS Windows it compiles under MinGW
- Under Mac OS X, to be able to produce static binary, you'll need to
compile wxWidgets accordingly [1]

[1] http://wiki.wxwidgets.org/Distributing_WxWidgets_Applications-Distributing_WxMac_Programs#Statically_compiling

